value.0: Your eyes open and you wince at the brightness of the flames about you. The sounds of battle are loud and close, as if buried within your skull. Blood seeps into the cool ground. You realize that it's yours.
The sounds of battle become increasingly muffled. From a long way off you can hear the Prince's dying words: "Tell the King that she is dead..."

With effort, your face turns skyward. The night breeze brushes against your skin, causing you to smile. This might be the most beautiful moment of your life. Your eyes slowly focus on the silhouette above you.
<StartAction>[Will Save: Failure]</Start> Panic wells up within you. You knew this man once. You called him your Prince and now he dangles before you, almost limp, at the end of a soldier's pike.
The broken man's eyes are blue and intense. His piercing stare burns itself into your memory. Slowly, he blinks.
"Don't you remember?" the Prince whispers, his words thick with blood. "We did it... to ourselves..." He coughs, the pain rolling his eyes back to bare their whites. "You must... tell the King..."

The Prince's eyes flash even brighter, as if daring you to proclaim his death. "You must... tell the King..." he whispers but the pain rolls his eyes back to bare their whites. Blood trickles from his mouth.

You find you cannot break the Prince's stare. His presence is commanding even as the blood pulses from between his lips. "You must... tell the King..." Coughing in pain, his eyes roll back to bare their whites.

<StartAction>[Will Save: Success]</Start> You feel a strange calm as you observe the broken body of a man you once called your Prince. His eyes, blue and intense, stare into yours. Slowly, the man blinks.
The man smiles, soft and horrible. "Don't you see, <FirstName>? We have... We have already won..."
"Please..." he whispers, his smile soft but gruesome.
Blood pulses from the corner of the Prince's lips. His voice is liquid. "You must... tell the King..." He coughs, the pain rolling his eyes back to bare their whites.
"Do not hate me... for what I have done, <FirstName>..."
"I know you are, <FirstName>... You always were."
Eyes closed now, his breathing labored, the broken man continues. "Tell the King that she is dead..."
Weary, you close your eyes, trying to will an end to the battle that surrounds you. Little by little the world falls to silence...
The Prince opens his eyes for the last time, staring into yours. The brilliant blue slowly fades to the color of dull ash. He'll answer no more questions in this life...
You wait for a long, long time. Far above you, the clouds part to reveal the night stars. Prince Ahmed is dead. Weary, you begin to count...

Still haunted by the events of last night, you keep a wary eye on Prince Ahmed's corpse. As the battle had raged around you, he said you were to "tell the King that she is dead." If only you knew what that meant...
He appears to have been stripped clean before being placed on the pike. Whoever did it to him left him with only his loincloth.
You pry the pike from the frozen earth and free the Prince from its ragged point.
The old woman eyes you nervously. "That one? No, not I. He already be stripped bare and pierced like that when I laid eyes on him... He's got a noble look, though, don't you think?"
Prince Ahmed's glassy-eyed corpse gazes up at you from the frozen ground. A gaping wound in his chest marks the place where the pike pierced him.
He appears to have been stripped clean before being placed on the pike. Whoever did it to him left him with only his loincloth.
You gather stones from the rocky ground and begin to pile them up around the Prince's broken body. It's long and backbreaking work.
As the cairn grows around the body of your prince, you begin to feel very alone. An icy mist is rolling in from the east horizon and you know it will envelop him. The thought of it leaves you numb.
At last the cairn is complete. The mists grow ever closer and a part of you knows that it's time to move on, to say goodbye, to let go. You swallow the lump in your throat and stand.
The old woman eyes you nervously. "That one? No, not I. He already be stripped bare and pierced like that when I laid eyes on him... He's got a noble look, though, don't you think?"
A rocky cairn has been erected on the spot where Prince Ahmed died. Mists gather around its base.

You feel at one with the man buried beneath the rock as you pray for his spirit's safety on its journey. As you pray, you experience the strange sensation of the Prince somehow doing the same for you.
Allow yourself to slip into unconsciousness.
Try to move your head.
"Who do this to us?!"
"Who did this to us?!"
"How you be alive like that?"
"You're alive?"
Close your eyes.
"We be losing this one, yuh Prince?"
"I take it the battle isn't going well..."
"Prince..."
"My liege..."
Wait for the man to talk.
"Huh? Tell me what you want me to tell King!"
"Tell the King what? What must I tell him?"
"Be strong. Me here for you."
"Hold strong, my Prince. I'm here."
Wait for him to continue.
Slip into unconsciousness.
"How you mean we do this to ourselves? Why we do that?"
"'We did this to ourselves...' But how? Why?"
"Was me really there for you, Prince? Always?"
"Was I really always there for you, my Prince?"
"How you mean we already win this battle?"
"What did you mean we've already won this battle?"
"How me ever hate you, Prince?"
"How could I ever hate you, Ahmed?"
"What happened? What you done?"
"What have you done?"
"She? Who you mean by that?"
"She? Who do you mean by 'she?' "
Wait...
Leave.
Search the Prince's corpse.
Take the Prince's body down from the pike.
"Ragpicker, did you search this one?"
Search the Prince's corpse.
Build a burial cairn for Prince Ahmed.
"Ragpicker, did you search this one?"
Pray for the Prince's spirit.
